==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hydrosphere
<hw>Hy"dro*sphere</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>hydro-</ets>, 1 + <ets>sphere</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Meteor.)</fld> <def>The aqueous vapor of the entire
atmosphere.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Phys. Geog.)</fld> <def>The aqueous envelope of the
earth, including the ocean, all lakes, streams, and underground waters,
and the aqueous vapor in the atmosphere.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hydrostat</ent>⟦br⟧
